    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for model risk level 3 and medium model influence. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted given the standardized ASTM F1717 protocol, two-laboratory validation design, and regulatory precedent. All three QoIs pass quantitative acceptance criteria (<10% difference, E/uval <1.96) across all 11 constructs. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as credible for its intended use in the regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw.",
